3. e4 {[%csl Gd4,Ge4]} { One of the main ideas in the Trompowsky against the line with 2...e6 is that White is willing to exchange his bishop on g5 for the knight on f6 in order to create a powerful center and control a lot of squares. } h6 { One of the most played moves at all levels. } 
4. Bxf6 Qxf6 
5. Nc3 ( { Here I give two recommendations for White: } 5.Nc3 { with complex, tactical play and the more solid } ) ( 5.c3 { . I would recommend you study both so you can mix it up if necessary, and your repertoire will not become too predictable. } ) ( { This move used to be the main move, but } 5.c3 { has seen a steady increase in popularity. The lines after } ) ( 5.Nc3 { can be quite complex. } ) d6 
