In the current position White's next moves are typically Nge2 or Nh3. The bishop can be traded on d3 and if Black plays Bd6 White can avoid the exchange with Bh4. After completing his development White can try to gain more space by either going for e3-e4 or f3-f4 followed by g4-g5.

In such positions, the c-file is bound to open up one way or another, so White should aim to make better use of it than their opponent. } *

