6. Nc3 { This is a kind of Pirc/Modern Defense position with White having the extra move f2-f3. this means he can no longer play a classical setup with a knight on f3 but it also means that if he goes for the sharp lines with queenside castling and attacking the black king he got the move f2-f3 (useful in supporting g2-g4) for free. So his attack will be one move faster than in the Pirc/Modern Defense, which makes it really dangerous for Black. } Bg7 
