14. Rc1 {[%cal Gb2b4,Gc4c5,Gb4b5]} { Objectively speaking the position is equal, but I think it is easier to play with White. White can continue with b2-b4 and then either c4-c5 and then after d6-d5 the move b4-b5 or immediately b4-b5 without c4-c5. Meanwhile for Black it is difficult to become active, White has prevented the main pawn breaks on the kingside and I don't see how to make sacrifices with Bxe3 or Nxg3 work. Especially the bishop on c8 is quite passive and most endgames will favor White. } *

