13. Na4 { Not with the idea to take on b6 but to put the knight on c5. } Kh8 { Black threatens to take on a4 and then on d5. } ( 13...Bxa4 { A big decision from Black to give up this bishop, but playable. } 14.Bxa4 Kh8 { Black could not take immediately 14...Nxd5? because of the pin after 15.Bb3 , but now he is threatening Nxd5, so White's next move is logical. } 15.Bb3 f5 16.a4 { Threatening to win the b6-bishop with a4-a5. } 16...a6 17.a5 Ba7 18.Rc1 { We have reached a complex position where I think White has tiny edge based on his pair of bishops. White's next moves could be Bc3 (or Be1 followed by Nc3 if Black plays Ne4), Qc2 and one day f2-f4 (after defending the pawn on e3 and playing Kh1 first) to open the long diagonal for the bishop. } ) 
