Because the bishop is on h4 far away from the queenside, there are quite a few lines where Black plays Qb6 with the idea to take on b2. These are complicated lines with very good winning chances for White and I will discuss them in great detail. } c5 { A direct attack on White's center. Black is trying to prove that the bishop on h4 is offside and that both d4 and b2 are now a bit weak. } 
