3. e3 {[%mdl 32768]} { Usually when Black plays c5 we answer with e3. We don't want to give away the center by taking on c5 and defending with Nf3 is not ideal because a knight on d4 can easily be chased away. White can sometimes answer c7-c5 with c2-c3, but that results in a symmetrical pawn structure after pawns are exchanged on d4 and I prefer to have a bit more imbalance. } f6 {[%cal Rg8h6,Rh6f5,Gg5h4]} 
4. Bf4 { Whenever Black plays f6 and still has the option of Nh6 we don't play Bh4 because a later Nh6-f5 would be annoying. } Nc6 ( 4...cxd4 5.exd4 Nc6 6.Nf3 Bg4 7.Be2 { is a transposition to the line with 4...Nc6 and 6...cxd4. } ) 
