16. Qxd5 { White now has an extra pawn, but this is only the beginning of large complications. } O-O-O {[%cal Gd8d5]} { Threatening Bxh2+. } 
17. Qxe4 Qxb2 
18. Nd2 { The only move to save the rook. } Rhe8 
19. Qg4+ Kb8 { Black has ideas like Bxh2+ followed by Rxd2, but also Ne5 can be annoying. } 
20. Nc4 Qxc2 
21. Nxd6 Rxe2 ( { Now on } 21...Rxd6 22.Qg3 { White can still play for an edge with his strong bishop. } ) 
22. Rfc1 {[%cal Rc2d2,Rc2b2,Gc1d1,Ga1b1,Gb1a1,Gc1b1]} { There is a draw possible here with the Black queen staying on the second rank and the white rooks keep attacking the queen. } *

