4. e3 {[%cal Gd1h5]} { Threatening Qh5 mate! } Nf6 { The old main line of 2. Bg5, but after this move White can count on a clear advantage. } 
5. Bg3 d6 
6. h4 Rg8 { I am not sure whether this is playable for Black with so many weakened light squares. } ( { If instead of 6...Rg8 Black plays } 6...g4 { , White can continue with } 7.Bc4 { and Ne2. } ) 
