10. Bh5+ Kd7 
11. Bf7 {[%cal Gf7e6,Gf7g8][%csl Rg8]} { Isn't it wonderful when you can play such a move? } Rg7 
12. Be6+ Ke8 
13. Bxc8 Qxc8 
14. Ne2 {[%cal Ge2d4,Gb1c3,Gd4e6,Gd4f5,Gd1d3][%csl Re6,Re8]} { This looks quite bad for Black. His king has lost the right to castle, his bishop on f8 is passive, the knight on a6 offside and there is a big hole on e6 for a white knight. So White's next moves will be Nbc3, Nd4, and if Black defends with c6 and Nc7, White may play Qd3 and Nxf5. } *

