13. Bd3 Ne4 {[%cal Gd2b3]} ( { After } 13...Nh5 { White plays } 14.N2b3 { defending the pawn on c5 while not being afraid of exchanging on g3, because after White castles kingside the pawn on f5 and next the pawn on g4 are likely to fall. } ) 
