1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} Nf6 
2. Bg5 { It is funny to see that creative Ivanchuk plays this opening against the even more creative Jobava! } Ne4 
3. Bf4 d5 
4. e3 ( 4.f3 Nf6 5.Nc3 { is the recommendation in the repertoire. } ) c5 
5. Bd3 Nc6 
6. Bxe4 { An old line, no advantage for White but of course Black can make mistakes. } dxe4 
7. d5 Nb4 { Instead g5 or even e5 are the engines recommendations. } 
8. Nc3 e6 
9. d6 { A fantastic passed pawn but White needs to work hard to keep it strong because one mistake and the pawn becomes weak. } Nc6 
10. Nge2 { Taking the pawn brings no advantage: } ( 10.Nxe4 e5 11.Bg5 Qd7 12.Nxc5 { Other moves are possible as well but no advantage either. } 12...Qxd6 13.Qxd6 Bxd6 14.Ne4 { And Black probably has sufficient compensation for the pawn. } ) f5 { Bd7 is the move Black should have played. } 
11. Nb5 Kf7 
12. Nc7 { White could also immediately have played } ( 12.g4! g5 13.gxf5 gxf4 14.Nxf4 { And Black is close to lost. } ) Rb8 
13. g4 { Very strong, attack over the light squares. } fxg4 
14. Ng3 Nb4 
15. a3 Nd5 
16. Nxe4 { Simple chess: taking a pawn and defending d6. } Nxf4 
17. exf4 Kg8 
18. Qxg4 { Just look at this position, Black is comepletely lost, White hasn't even sacrificed anything! } h5 
19. Qg3 b5 
20. Rg1 { Adding pieces to the attack and... } Rh6 
21. O-O-O { never forget about king safety. } Kh8 
22. Nxc5 { Basically game over. } b4 
23. axb4 Rxb4 
24. d7 Rc4 
25. N5xe6 { Black resigned, he is losing a lot of material or gets mated. } 1-0

