1. d4 {[%mdl 32768]} d5 
2. Bg5 { The Pseudo-Trompowsky. } h6 
3. Bh4 c5 { Black is playing one of the main systems. } 
4. Nc3 { Not recommened to do this with White! } Nc6 
5. Nf3 Bg4 
6. Ne5 cxd4 { Not a great move. Black could have gained some advantage here: } ( 6...g5 7.Bg3 Bg7 8.Nxc6 bxc6 { with a lot of pressure on d4. } ) 
7. Nxc6 bxc6 
8. Qxd4 { White is happy again! } Qb6 { A sharp move but also the best one in the position. } 
9. Qxg4 { White had an alternative in } ( 9.O-O-O Rb8 10.b3 Bd7 11.e4 e6 { with mutual chances, White is ahead in development but it is not easy to open lines against Black's king. } ) Qxb2 
10. Nd1 { Forced. } Qxa1 
11. Qa4 { This was White's idea when sacrificing the exchange. } Rc8 
12. e4 { Principled play from White, opening lines against Black's king but the engine prefers the more modest e3 followed by Ba6. } Nf6 { Black is suddenly winning. } 
13. Ba6 Nxe4 
14. O-O Nc5 { A bad mistake. After } ( 14...Rc7 { White doesn't have sufficient compensation. If he attacks the pawn on c6 Black can even defend with Kd7 and opening lines with c4 is met by the simple Qd4 followed by e6. } ) 
15. Qa3 { Suddenly the black queen is in trouble, I am sure Black missed the idea of queen moving backwards followed by Nc3 or Nb2. } Nxa6 ( 15...Qd4 16.Bxc8 { And White is a piece up. } ) 
16. Nc3 Qxf1+ 
17. Kxf1 Nc7 { Another mistake. } 
18. Qxa7 { Now Qb7 is a threat, if the knight would have been on b8 Black could play Rd8 and rook, knight and pawn on c6 are all still defended. } Nb5 
19. Nxb5 cxb5 
20. Qb7 { Black wished he had casled already. } Rc5 
21. Qb6 Rxc2 
22. Qxb5+ { and soon the rook will be lost via a few checks. } 1-0

